==English==
===Etymology===
From the Latin [[rapare]], to take away or snatch out.

===Noun===
'''rapture'''

# Extreme pleasure and happiness or excitement

# The Rapture (proper noun): Sudden removal of Christian believers from the Earth before the Tribulation and the return of Jesus Christ.

===Common Uses===
# '''In reference to original meaning, i.e. to take away, snatch out:'''
# I'm off to rapture your laptop.

# '''In reference to extreme happiness:'''
# My new car fills me with a sense of rapture... (and was later 'raptured' from the driveway)


